{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "HoltslagBovilleNonlocalABL",
        "description": "Nonlocal atmospheric boundary-layer diffusion scheme of Holtslag & Boville (1993). Given the height z, boundary-layer depth h, friction velocity u_star, surface virtual heat flux wθ_v0, surface scalar flux wC_0, surface virtual potential temperature θ_v0 and Obukhov length L, it computes the convective velocity scale w_star, the φ_m/φ_h Monin-Obukhov similarity profiles, the momentum and scalar velocity scales w_m/w_t, the turbulent Prandtl number Pr, the eddy-diffusivity profile Kc = κ·w_t·z·(1−z/h)² and the countergradient nonlocal transport term γc. The nonlocal scheme represents transport by large convective eddies that the local scheme cannot. Migrated from AtmosphericDynamics.jl@816cc391 src/holtslag_boville_1993.jl:290 (`HoltslagBovilleNonlocalABL` @component); algebraic (observed-only) — the 7 inputs are parameters, the 14 turbulence quantities are algebraic state variables, no ODE integration.",
        "tags": [
            "atmospheric_dynamics",
            "holtslag-boville",
            "boundary-layer",
            "turbulence",
            "eddy-diffusivity",
            "observed-only"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-17T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "AtmosphericDynamics.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-4dgr)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Holtslag, A. A. M., & Boville, B. A. (1993). Local Versus Nonlocal Boundary-Layer Diffusion in a Global Climate Model. Journal of Climate, 6(10), 1825-1842.",
                "doi": "10.1175/1520-0442(1993)006<1825:LVNBLD>2.0.CO;2"
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "HoltslagBovilleNonlocalABL": {
            "reference": {
                "doi": "10.1175/1520-0442(1993)006<1825:LVNBLD>2.0.CO;2",
                "citation": "Holtslag & Boville, 1993",
                "notes": "source_ref: AtmosphericDynamics.jl@816cc3918e1eef2c2ee6d8fa8dd73c8f13a85a47:src/holtslag_boville_1993.jl:290\nUpstream `HoltslagBovilleNonlocalABL` is an MTK `@component` that returns `System(eqs, t)` with 14 time-indexed `@variables`, each fixed by one algebraic equation (no time derivative appears), and 7 `@parameters` of inputs. It is migrated as an algebraic (observed-only) model: the 7 inputs are `parameter`s, the 14 turbulence quantities are `state` variables defined by the algebraic `equations` — the same serialization pattern as components/atmospheric_dynamics/sp_ch1/ideal_gas.esm and components/wildland_fire/rothermel/wind_limit.esm. No ODE integration occurs; tests assert the closed-form solution at t=0.\nThe 11 upstream `@constants` (g, κ, a_coeff, c_1, ε_sl, w_ref, zero_heat_flux, zero_length, γc_zero, zero_velocity, L_min) are preserved as `parameter` declarations with their upstream defaults, matching the MTK-`@constants`-to-ESM-`parameter` convention used in wind_limit.esm. The `zero_heat_flux`/`zero_length`/`zero_velocity`/`γc_zero` constants are kept rather than inlined as `0.0` literals so the `ifelse` comparison operands and stable-branch values carry units matching the quantities they are compared with (K*m/s, m, m/s, 1/m).\nVariable names: Unicode subscripts in the upstream identifiers are transliterated to ASCII (φₕ→φ_h, φₘ→φ_m, φₕ_local→φ_h_local, φₘ_local→φ_m_local, wₘ→w_m, wₘ_outer→w_m_outer, wₜ→w_t, wθᵥ₀→wθ_v0, wC₀→wC_0, θᵥ₀→θ_v0, c₁→c_1); Greek base letters (φ, ζ, η, κ, ε, γ, θ) are retained, following the convention in components/urban_canopy/urban_radiation.esm.\nRegularization: ζ = z/L and ζ_ε = ε_sl·h/L are guarded for small |L| — when abs(L) ≤ L_min the denominator L is replaced by a value of magnitude L_min carrying L's sign. Upstream encodes this branchlessly as L_min·sign(L) + L_min·(1−abs(sign(L))); it is re-expressed here as the mathematically identical ifelse(L < 0, −L_min, L_min) because the ESS Julia MTK binding (EarthSciSerializationMTKExt.jl) does not implement the `sign` operator that esm-spec §4.2 lists — the two forms agree exactly for L>0 (+L_min), L<0 (−L_min) and L=0 (+L_min). The regularized branch is never selected by the inline tests (all use |L| ≥ 50 m); it only needs to compile and stay finite.\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-6): observed-only algebraic system (no ODE integration); every output is a closed-form composition of arithmetic, sqrt, cube-root (^1/3) and ifelse selections in float64. 1e-6 is far above float64 round-off accumulated over the ~10-deep expression chains (w_t depends on w_m and Pr, which depend on the φ profiles and w_star) and below any physical-discrimination scale on the m/s, m^2/s and 1/m output quantities. Exact-zero expectations (w_star and γc in stable conditions, where the `ifelse` selects the zero-velocity / γc_zero constant) carry a per-assertion abs=1e-12 tolerance."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1e-06
            },
            "variables": {
                "z": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 100.0,
                    "description": "Height above surface"
                },
                "h": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 1000.0,
                    "description": "Boundary layer height"
                },
                "u_star": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "default": 0.3,
                    "description": "Friction velocity"
                },
                "wθ_v0": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K*m/s",
                    "default": 0.05,
                    "description": "Surface virtual heat flux (w'θ_v')_0"
                },
                "wC_0": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "default": 1e-05,
                    "description": "Surface kinematic flux of scalar C (e.g. mixing ratio)"
                },
                "θ_v0": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 300.0,
                    "description": "Virtual potential temperature at surface"
                },
                "L": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": -100.0,
                    "description": "Obukhov length (negative for unstable, positive for stable)"
                },
                "g": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s^2",
                    "default": 9.81,
                    "description": "Gravitational acceleration"
                },
                "κ": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.4,
                    "description": "von Karman constant"
                },
                "a_coeff": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 7.2,
                    "description": "Nonlocal transport constant (Eq. A14: a ≈ 7.2)"
                },
                "c_1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.6,
                    "description": "Velocity scale constant (Eq. A11)"
                },
                "ε_sl": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.1,
                    "description": "Surface layer fraction of boundary layer height"
                },
                "w_ref": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Reference velocity scale for non-dimensionalizing the cube-root arguments"
                },
                "zero_heat_flux": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K*m/s",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Zero heat flux, comparison constant for the unstable/stable branch"
                },
                "zero_length": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Zero length, comparison constant for the L sign branch"
                },
                "γc_zero": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1/m",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Zero nonlocal transport term (stable-branch value of γc)"
                },
                "zero_velocity": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Zero velocity (stable-branch value of w_star)"
                },
                "L_min": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Minimum absolute Obukhov length for regularization of z/L"
                },
                "ζ": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Stability parameter z/L at local height"
                },
                "η": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Relative height z/h"
                },
                "ζ_ε": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Stability parameter ε_sl·h/L at the surface layer top"
                },
                "w_star": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "description": "Convective velocity scale (Eq. A12)"
                },
                "φ_m": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Dimensionless wind shear at the surface layer top (Eq. A2/A4/A8)"
                },
                "φ_h": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Dimensionless temperature gradient at the surface layer top (Eq. A3/A5/A6)"
                },
                "φ_h_local": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Dimensionless temperature gradient at local height z (Eq. A3/A5/A6)"
                },
                "φ_m_local": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Dimensionless wind shear at local height z (Eq. A2/A4/A8)"
                },
                "w_m_outer": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "description": "Outer-layer momentum velocity scale (Eq. A11)"
                },
                "w_m": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "description": "Velocity scale for momentum, height-dependent (Eq. A7/A11)"
                },
                "Pr": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Turbulent Prandtl number (Eq. A13)"
                },
                "w_t": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "description": "Velocity scale for scalars, height-dependent (Eq. A1/A10)"
                },
                "Kc": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m^2/s",
                    "description": "Eddy diffusivity profile (Eq. 3.9)"
                },
                "γc": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1/m",
                    "description": "Nonlocal countergradient transport term (Eq. 3.10)"
                }
            },
